HEADWORD: Pogamoggan
<hw>Pog`a*mog"gan</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[North Amer.
Indian.]</ety> <def>An aboriginal weapon consisting of a stone or piece
of antler fastened to the end of a slender wooden handle, used by
American Indians from the Great Plains to the Mackenzie River.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

